# Security Rules

## Authentication

- JWT `access_token` (15 min) + `refresh_token` (7 days) — both httpOnly cookies
- Cookie flags: `httpOnly: true`, `sameSite: "lax"`, `secure: true` (production)
- `requireAuth` middleware validates `access_token` on every protected backend route
- Frontend `middleware.ts` blocks `/admin/*` (except `/login`) without valid cookie
- Frontend `(admin)/layout.tsx` calls `requireAdmin()` — double guard

## Password Security

```ts
// ✅ Always bcrypt
import bcrypt from "bcryptjs";
const hash = await bcrypt.hash(password, 12);
const match = await bcrypt.compare(plain, hash);

// ❌ Never
user.password === inputPassword // plaintext compare — never
```

Passwords are stored in `users` table only — never in `site_settings`.

## Input Validation

```ts
// ✅ Always validate before service call
const parsed = CreateLeadBody.safeParse(req.body);
if (!parsed.success) { res.status(400).json({ error: "Invalid body" }); return; }
const lead = await createLead(parsed.data);

// ✅ Always parse ID params
const id = parseIdParam(req, res); // returns null and sends 400 if NaN
if (id === null) return;
```

## CORS

- `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` env var — never wildcard `*`
- `credentials: true` — required for cookie-based auth
- Frontend origin must be in `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` on backend

## Admin Endpoints — All Must Have requireAuth

```ts
// ✅ Protected
router.get(ROUTE_PATHS.LEADS.LIST, requireAuth, async (req, res) => { ... });

// ❌ Unprotected admin route — never
router.get(ROUTE_PATHS.LEADS.LIST, async (req, res) => { ... });
```

## Frontend Secrets

- Never use `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix for secrets — only truly public config values
- JWT secrets stay server-side only (`JWT_ACCESS_SECRET`, `JWT_REFRESH_SECRET`)
- Admin credentials (`ADMIN_EMAIL`, `ADMIN_PASSWORD`) — backend `.env` only
